               <sense xml:id="Dmain" xml:lang="la" source="#dillmann"> et <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሐሜላት፡</foreign> <gramGrp> <pos expand="Substantivum">subst.</pos> </gramGrp>, est graecum <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἡ μηλωτή</foreign> cum articulo, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> pellis hispida </t:quote></cit> (ovina), <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> melote </t:quote></cit> (syr. <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܡܺܝܠܬܳܐ</foreign>‌‌‍) <ref cRef="3 Reg." loc="19,13">3 Reg. 19,13</ref>; <ref cRef="3 Reg." loc="19,19">3 Reg. 19,19</ref>; <ref cRef="4 Reg." loc="2,8">4 Reg. 2,8</ref>; <ref cRef="4 Reg." loc="2,13">4 Reg. 2,13</ref>; <ref cRef="4 Reg." loc="2,14">4 Reg. 2,14</ref>; <ref cRef="Hebr." loc="11,37">Hebr. 11,37</ref>. Hoc nomine <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> melote </t:quote></cit> vel <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> cucullus </t:quote></cit> monachorum appellari solet, in libris, ubi de monachorum vita agitur. </sense>
               
